						<summary>

						<p>On a pillar in the <hi rend="italic">mukha-maṇḍapa</hi> of the Mallikārjuna temple.</p>						

						<p>Achyuta, 1531 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1452, Vikṛiti, Pushya ba. 11, Saturday,</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">1531 A.D., January 14.</hi></p>						

						<p>It registers the gift of fly-whisks to the god Mallikārjuna and laced cloth and eye � to the goddess Bhramarāṁba by Māḷapa-nāyaka, the <hi rend="italic">ūḷigam</hi> of the king for the merit of his overlord (Achyuta) and Kṛishṇarāya.</p>						

